The paper deals with optimization of resource allocation in a stochastic scenario involving multiple agents, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of probability distributions and Monte Carlo methods suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA). The analytical method used in the paper involves approximations to Gaussian distributions, which is a common technique in statistical learning (cs.LG).
